gomodel:SYNGO_5278  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 5: \"The adaptor protein Fe65 (APBB1) is present in Schaffer collaterals/CA1 dendritic spine hippocampal synapses where it colocalizes with P2X2 subunits. Immunogold localization of Fe65 using Fe65-32 (A-C) or Fe65-35 (D-G) antibodies. Gold particles were found both at the pre- and postsynaptic specialization of excitatory hippocampal synapses.\". Experimental description: M&M: \"Light and Electron Microscopy\nFour postnatal day 35 Sprague-Dawley rats were transcardially perfused. \"\n\nantibody:\n\"Polyclonal antibodies were raised in rabbits using the GST fusion protein containing amino acids 197-255 or amino acids 40-100 of Fe65 (antibodies Fe65-32 or -35, respectively).\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-09" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5278" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

